This Privacy Policy describes how and when we (Smart Track Telematics Ltd. T/A Smart Track) collect, use and share your information across our website and App. When using our website and App you consent to the collection, transfer, storage, disclosure, and use of your information as described in this Privacy Policy. You can be sure that we will only use your information as described in this Privacy Policy.
What data do we collect?
We collect personal data from customer accounts and their employees, website visitors, applicants, end users, and APP users (mobile app service). The data collected may include: name, email address, location address and telephone numbers, company name, individual contact names and job titles, IP addresses, device identification and devise location information, service and site usage information. We could request other information depending on the services you require from us, this could for example be services being ordered by you.
For customers who use our fleet management services we also collect vehicle and driving information, including information such as location, (date/time) and speed and driver identification.
Smart Track may use “cookies” and likewise technology to obtain information about your visits to our website. If you contact us we ask you for some information to identify you. This helps us determine which parts of our web sites or e-mails are of interest, help us improve the quality and usefulness of our site, and personalize your experience.
Use of cookies may also allow us to automate entry into password-protected portions of our website so that you will not need to re-enter your password each time you visit our website. You can block cookies (if you want to) through your internet browser or other software available, but if you chose to do so you may make some of our services/features unavailable to you. Some features might not be affected by browser controls.
How do we collect personal data?
We may collect personal data in a number of ways, including from orders forms filled out by customers, from end users, (whether by telephone, e-mail, internet or contract form), from apps, enquiries made by existing customers, word of mouth and potential customers.
